This paper deals with issue tracking systems in software development, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze the text of issue descriptions, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses machine learning models to predict issue types, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the practical applications of issue type prediction, which could fall under cybernetics (cs.CY).
